      "title": "Journal of Futuristic Urbanism, Smart Societies, and Technological Innovation",
      "iconClass": "fa-book",
      "articles": [
        {
          "title": "Computational Creativity in Digital Performance Art",
          "iconClass": "fa-palette",
          "fullContent": "<p>This article explores how generative AI and real-time algorithms are transforming digital performance art. We analyze three case studies where choreographers collaborated with machine learning models to create adaptive dance routines. The research shows that computational creativity does not replace human artists but rather augments their expressive capabilities, leading to novel forms of audience interaction.</p><h3>Key Findings</h3><ul><li>AI-generated choreography reduced production time by 40%.</li><li>Audience engagement scores increased by 25% in interactive performances.</li><li>Legal frameworks for authorship remain ambiguous for co-created works.</li></ul><p>We conclude with recommendations for copyright reform to recognize hybrid human-AI creations.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Algorithmic Aesthetics: Machine Learning in Visual Arts",
          "iconClass": "fa-robot",
          "fullContent": "<p>This paper examines the aesthetic principles emerging from deep learning models used in visual art generation. Through a survey of 500 digital artists, we identify common patterns in AI-generated imagery and evaluate their reception in galleries and auction houses. The study also addresses legal disputes over ownership of AI-generated artworks.</p><h3>Conclusion</h3><p>While AI can mimic existing styles, true novelty remains a human domain. We propose a three-tier attribution system for human-AI collaborative works.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Media Convergence and Cultural Identity in the Digital Age",
          "iconClass": "fa-film",
          "fullContent": "<p>This interdisciplinary study analyzes how streaming platforms and social media algorithms shape cultural identity formation. Using ethnographic data from young adults in three countries, we show that algorithmic recommendations often reinforce dominant cultural narratives, sometimes at the expense of local heritage. The article concludes with policy recommendations for media pluralism.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Interdisciplinary Approaches to AI-Generated Music",
          "iconClass": "fa-music",
          "fullContent": "<p>We present a framework for evaluating AI-composed music based on musicological, legal, and computational criteria. Our analysis of 200 AI-generated compositions reveals that while structural coherence is high, emotional expressiveness lags behind human compositions. The article also discusses copyright implications for AI-generated sound recordings.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ethics of Generative Art: Authorship and Authenticity",
          "iconClass": "fa-feather-alt",
          "fullContent": "<p>This philosophical inquiry addresses the ethical dimensions of generative art, focusing on questions of authorship, authenticity, and value. We argue that current legal definitions of 'originality' are inadequate for AI-generated works. A new framework based on 'curatorial contribution' is proposed to assign rights between human prompters and AI systems.</p>"
        }
      ],
