      "articles": [
        {
          "title": "COP28 Loss and Damage Fund: Legal Architecture and Operationalization",
          "iconClass": "fa-coins",
          "fullContent": "<p>This article analyzes the legal architecture of the Loss and Damage Fund established at COP28. We examine funding sources, governance, eligibility criteria, and distribution mechanisms. The article identifies challenges, including additionality and host country consent.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Historical Emitters Liability Under International Environmental Law",
          "iconClass": "fa-gavel",
          "fullContent": "<p>We examine whether historical emitters can be held liable for climate-related loss and damage under principles of state responsibility and international tort law. The article reviews arguments based on transboundary harm and the no-harm rule.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Developing Country Access to Climate Finance Mechanisms",
          "iconClass": "fa-donate",
          "fullContent": "<p>This paper assesses the barriers faced by developing countries in accessing climate finance for loss and damage. We propose reforms to the Green Climate Fund and the creation of a fast-track procedure for vulnerable nations.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Insurance Mechanisms for Climate Loss and Damage Claims",
          "iconClass": "fa-file-contract",
          "fullContent": "<p>We evaluate insurance-based solutions for loss and damage, including the African Risk Capacity and CCRIF. The article concludes that insurance is insufficient for non-economic losses and advocates for a hybrid grant-insurance model.</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Santiago Network: Technical Assistance for Loss and Damage",
          "iconClass": "fa-network-wired",
          "fullContent": "<p>This article analyzes the role of the Santiago Network in providing technical assistance for loss and damage. We review its governance structure, work program, and relationship with the new Loss and Damage Fund. Recommendations for strengthening the Network are provided.</p>"
        }
      ],
