          "fullContent": "<p>This article assesses whether carbon border adjustment mechanisms (CBAMs) violate WTO non-discrimination principles (GATT Articles I and III). We argue that CBAMs can be justified under GATT Article XX (environmental exception) if designed to avoid arbitrary discrimination. The analysis draws on the EU's CBAM proposal and recent WTO rulings on environmental measures (e.g., Brazil–Retreaded Tyres).</p>"
